6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Cohere and Inflection share a solid foundation of core features including File Upload, Api Access, Multilingual. Where Cohere pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Web Search and Citations, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Inflection uniquely offers Memory, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Cohere holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 5/10, while Inflection scores 6/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Cohere and Inflection offer flexible pricing models. Cohere has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Inflection does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
